A new date for Mr Mutura to take oath of office will be announced later.Despite spirited attempts to convince the judge to administer the oath, the judge declined. The planned swearing in of Nairobi County Assembly Speaker Benson Mutura as acting Nairobi County Governor has been postponed.
This is after the judge assigned to preside over the taking of oath of office arrived late for the ceremony.
According to the law, such an event should be performed between 10am and 2pm. However, the judge arrived a minute past 2pm resulting in the cancellation of the event.



