Despite spirited attempts to convince the judge to administer the oath, he declined saying his action thereof could be challenged in court as he would be going against the provisions of the law.
A new date for Mr Mutura to take oath of office will be announced later.
The former Makadara MP was to be sworn in as acting governor after Senate Speaker Ken Lusaka gazetted the impeachment of Governor Mike Sonko on Thursday.



